    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. It sounds pretty risky though. Are there any specific \"red flags\" or sneaky parts in a clause like that that I should keep an eye out for so I don't get caught off guard?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A major red flag is when the scope is too broad, which this clause seems to be, by covering \"any and all losses.\" You should look closely at the trigger events, which are usually limited to *your* breach or *your* negligence. If the clause tries to make you cover things the Disclosing Party did wrong, that's a massive trap—it's a poorly-drafted, overly aggressive clause, and you should try to negotiate it down. It's always best to ensure the indemnity is mutual, or at least clearly limited to your own actions.",
      "source": "target",
